      <description>&lt;p&gt;An attempt of a properly styled animated badge prompted by &lt;a href=&#34;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=39355465&#34;&gt;@jsiepkes&amp;rsquo;s comment&lt;/a&gt; on HN:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;data:image/gif;base64,&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inspect the page to copy the base64-encoded image or save as a file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/George_Santayana#Vol._I,_Reason_in_Common_Sense&#34;&gt;quote&lt;/a&gt; by George Santanaya:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Progress, far from consisting in change, depends on retentiveness. When change is absolute there remains no being to improve and no direction is set for possible improvement: and when experience is not retained, as among savages, infancy is perpetual. Those who cannot remember the past are condemned to repeat it.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
